translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_7fb4ce7f:
    # "Sarah knew the answer before she dared to speak it."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_94b773e6:
    # "There could be no other but her."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_a2086a54:
    # "She was the most gifted, and above all, had the best temperament for it."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_11c143dc:
    # "Now to convince the others."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_7fc0cfce:
    # "Sarah knew almost instantly that it could not be her."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_74422886:
    # "They would need a strong leader, she knew that much, but out of all them she had the least experience."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_36422558:
    # "Then again, there was power in being able to leverage her vote for another."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_53067dd1:
    # "She had no doubt that the others would all be eager to put themselves up first."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_37ae5016:
    # "She could go into the negotiations, having something to offer rather than something to ask."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_5cf18f7e:
    # "Sarah knew it could not be her."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_f70e0a21:
    # "In fact, she knew it couldn't be any of them."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_589996c3:
    # "Each of them had a weakness to them. A flaw. To raise a single one of them up above the others would only invite disaster."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_1998a5d6:
    # "Sarah would have to convince the others to see it the same as her."
    ""

translate ru UnionLeaderPosition_8aef378f:
    # "To understand they would have the rule the Union as a council."
    ""

